Query: I've written a test case in Rust that involves serialization and deserialization using serde. One of the tests, `serialisation`, fails with an error. Here is the code:

```rust
use serde::{Serialize, Serializer};

#[derive(Debug, PartialEq, Eq, PartialOrd, Ord)]
struct Incline {
    rise: u8,
    distance: u8,
}

impl Incline {
    pub fn new(rise: u8, distance: u8) -> Incline {
        Incline {rise, distance}
    }
}

impl Serialize for Incline {
    fn serialize<S>(&self, serializer: S) -> Result<S::Ok, S::Error>
    where
        S: Serializer,
    {
        serializer.serialize_str(&format!("{}:{}", self.rise, self.distance))
    }
}

#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use std::collections::BTreeMap;
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn serialisation() {
        let key = Incline::new(4, 3);
        let value = "a steep hill";

        let mut map: BTreeMap<Incline, &str> = BTreeMap::new();
        map.insert(key, value);
        let serialised = serde_json::to_string(&map).unwrap();

        assert_eq!(serialised, r#"{"4:3":"a steep hill"}"#);
    }
}
```

The error message I'm getting is: `called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value: Error("key must be a string", line: 0, column: 0)`. How do I tell serde_json to use `Incline`'s implementation of `std::fmt::Display::fmt` to turn the `Incline::new(4,3)` into "4:3"?

